Application of Learning Answers
1.1 Directory Management using CMD

As a system administrator, I used CMD to manage directories:

Create directory
mkdir FolderName
Change directory
cd FolderName
cd ..
Rename directory
ren OldName NewName
Delete directory
rmdir FolderName

👉 These commands help organize and manage the server efficiently.

1.2 Git Setup and Configuration
Install Git → Download from git-scm.com
Verify installation
git --version
Initialize repository
cd XYZ_Project
git init
Create .gitignore
nano .gitignore

Add:

.env
.env.*
Save and commit
git add .
git commit -m "initial setup"

👉 This ensures version control and protects sensitive files.

1.3 Using GitHub for Project Collaboration
Set up project folder
mkdir FinanceApp
cd FinanceApp
Initialize Git
git init
Create GitHub repository (on github.com)
Link to GitHub
git remote add origin https://github.com/username/repo.git
Add files
git add .
git commit -m "first commit"
Push to GitHub
git push -u origin main
Collaborate
Use branches
Pull updates
Push changes
2.1 Checking Changes in Git
Check status:
git status

👉 shows:

feature.html → untracked
main.html → modified
View changes:
git diff main.html
Add files:
git add feature.html main.html
Delete unnecessary file:
rm filename

👉 Helps track and review changes before committing.

2.2 Branching and Collaboration
Create branch:
git branch feature-xyz
Switch branch:
git checkout feature-xyz
View branches:
git branch
Merge updates:
git checkout main
git pull
git checkout feature-xyz
git merge main

👉 This helps teamwork, tracking progress, and avoiding conflicts.

3.1 Working with Remote Repositories
Clone repository:
git clone repo_url
Fetch branch:
git fetch origin branch-name
Sync all branches:
git fetch --all
Pull updates:
git pull
Pull specific branch:
git pull origin branch-name
Force pull:
git pull --force

👉 Keeps local project updated with remote repository.

3.2 Pushing and Managing Remote Branches
Push to remote:
git push origin main
Force push:
git push --force
Verbose push:
git push -v
Delete remote branch:
git push origin --delete branch-name

👉 Helps share work, fix conflicts, and keep repo clean.

3.3 Rebase, Pull Request, and Merge
Rebase:
git checkout feature-branch
git rebase main

👉 Updates branch with latest code

Create Pull Request → on GitHub
Merge after approval:
git merge feature-branch

👉 Ensures clean integration and collaboration.

✅ FINAL SUMMARY
CMD → manage directories
Git → track changes
GitHub → collaboration
Branching → teamwork
Pull/Push → sync work
Merge/Rebase → combine code
